ahlers.phantom.embedded.processes

Interface IPhantomConsole

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    WriterPhantomConsole

    public interface IPhantomConsole
    Implementations provide access for writing to standard in on a running Phantom process. Compliment with an IStreamProcessor references (typically provided to PhantomProcess by the ProcessOutput assigned to IRuntimeConfig) to receive standard out and error. This interface's behavior is intentionally modeled after similar stream classes, like OutputStream or Writer. Be sure to see PhantomProcess.getConsole() for more specific behavior.
    See Also:
    RuntimeConfigBuilder.processOutput(ProcessOutput), ProcessOutput.getOutput(), ProcessOutput.getError(), PhantomProcess.getConsole()
